---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="kraft-heinz">
  <Fragment slot="meta">
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Kraft Heinz via Imaginary Content</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Feb 2020 – Oct 2021</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Art Director</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">CPG / Enterprise eCommerce</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Lead Brand</div><div class="cs-meta-value">MiO</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">~8%</div><div class="stat-label">Amazon sales lift, MiO YoY</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">$143K</div><div class="stat-label">Brand Store sales generated</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">39</div><div class="stat-label">SKUs supported</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Promo</div>
    <div class="media-video">
      <video src="/Images/MiO/MiO_09c.mp4" controls playsinline preload="metadata"></video>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-kh-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-kh-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Strong brand. Fragmented shelf.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">MiO had strong brand recognition, but its digital shelf was not converting as efficiently as it should have. The Amazon Brand Store was outdated, A+ content lacked structure, and Kroger placements were inconsistent. Creative was being adapted channel by channel without unified conversion logic.<br /><br />This was not just a design issue. It was revenue leakage.<br /><br />Kraft Heinz's consumer decision tree showed that flavor, sugar claims, and nutrition callouts were the top purchase drivers — but the shelf was not structured around any of them. The problem was not a lack of assets. It was a mismatch between what shoppers cared about and what the shelf emphasized.<br /><br />MiO's target consumer — the 'Pleasure Hacker' seeking bold flavor without guilt — was not being served within the first scroll.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-kh-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Rebuilt the shelf as a system, not a set of assets.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">The goal was to replace fragmented execution with a unified system structured around how MiO shoppers actually make decisions.<br /><br /><strong>A. Amazon A+ Content</strong> — Rebuilt as a conversion system mapped to the decision tree: value prop above the fold, competitive comparison (0g sugar / 0 calories vs juice, soda, energy drinks), product line breakdowns, and FAQ content sourced from Amazon Q&amp;A to reduce friction.<br /><br /><strong>B. Amazon Brand Store</strong> — Designed as a discovery-to-purchase funnel across desktop and mobile, guiding users from brand understanding to product selection through structured navigation and clear product hierarchy.<br /><br /><strong>C. Multi-Channel Creative System</strong> — Built a scalable system across Kroger banners, Amazon merch banners, programmatic display, and carousel images for all SKUs. Each carousel followed a structured sequence: hero, brand moment, use case, comparison, portfolio, servings, sub-brand message, and review.<br /><br /><strong>D. Video and Motion</strong> — Storyboarded and produced animated product video for A+ environments, translating product use into fast, visual communication.<br /><br /><strong>E. Team and Execution</strong> — Directed a production designer and junior designer across eCommerce, programmatic, retail media, and social.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-kh-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Measurable lift, honest attribution.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">The MiO digital shelf redesign contributed to a ~8% Amazon sales lift, year-over-year. The lift occurred during the redesign window I led across A+ content, Amazon Brand Store, retailer pages, and multi-channel creative. Reported through Kraft Heinz internal analytics.<br /><br />The MiO Brand Store generated $143,620 in sales from 108,287 visitors and 10,608 orders, with an average of 2.72 units per order.<br /><br />Sponsored Brands drove $84,406 in sales from 27,398 visits. Organic traffic contributed $42,491 from 15,868 visits.<br /><br />The Original sub-brand page led performance at $48,939, followed by Energy ($21,585) and Sport ($17,394).<br /><br />374 digital assets shipped across 39 SKUs spanning eCommerce, programmatic, and retail channels.<br /><br />More importantly, the work replaced fragmented execution with a consistent conversion framework grounded in shopper decision data.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Selected work</div>
    <div class="media-stack">
      <figure class="media-figure"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-banner-fixed-water.webp" alt="MiO 'We Fixed Water' banner" loading="lazy" /></figure>
      <figure class="media-figure"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-amazon-store-mock.webp" alt="MiO Amazon Brand Store desktop mockup" loading="lazy" /></figure>
      <div class="media-carousel" data-carousel>
        <div class="carousel-thumbs" data-carousel-thumbs>
          <button class="carousel-thumb active" type="button" data-index="0" aria-label="Show slide 1"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-1.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="1" aria-label="Show slide 2"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-2.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="2" aria-label="Show slide 3"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-3.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="3" aria-label="Show slide 4"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-4.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="4" aria-label="Show slide 5"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-5.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="5" aria-label="Show slide 6"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-6.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
          <button class="carousel-thumb" type="button" data-index="6" aria-label="Show slide 7"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-7.webp" alt="" loading="lazy" /></button>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-main">
          <button class="carousel-arrow prev" type="button" aria-label="Previous slide" data-carousel-prev>‹</button>
          <div class="carousel-track" data-carousel-track>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-1.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 1" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-2.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 2" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-3.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 3" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-4.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 4" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-5.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 5" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-6.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 6" loading="lazy" /></div>
            <div class="carousel-slide"><img src="/Images/MiO/mio-carousel-7.webp" alt="MiO carousel slide 7" loading="lazy" /></div>
          </div>
          <button class="carousel-arrow next" type="button" aria-label="Next slide" data-carousel-next>›</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Key Insight</div>
    <div class="foundation-card key-insight" style="border:none">
      <div class="foundation-section-title">Most teams treat the digital shelf as production. The teams that convert treat it as a system.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc">The lift did not come from better design. It came from aligning shopper decision data, brand storytelling, conversion UX, and platform constraints into one system.</div>
      <div class="foundation-desc" style="margin-bottom:0">Each asset was structured to help a specific shopper make a specific decision in a specific channel. That alignment is what turned the shelf into a revenue system.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="footer-prelude" style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text3);font-style:italic;line-height:1.55;max-width:650px;margin-bottom:24px">Sales lift based on internal Kraft Heinz reporting, YoY same-period for MiO. Brand Store performance based on Amazon Brand Analytics. Contribution tied to the digital shelf redesign window; cannot isolate from pricing, media spend, or competitive dynamics.</div>
</CaseStudy>
